27VideoRtpReceiver::VideoRtpReceiver(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
28 std::string receiver_id,
29 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids)
30 : VideoRtpReceiver(worker_thread,
31 receiver_id,
32 CreateStreamsFromIds(std::move(stream_ids))) {}
33
34VideoRtpReceiver::VideoRtpReceiver(
35 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
36 const std::string& receiver_id,
37 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>& streams)
38 : worker_thread_(worker_thread),
39 id_(receiver_id),
40 source_(rtc::make_ref_counted<VideoRtpTrackSource>(&source_callback_)),
41 track_(VideoTrackProxyWithInternal<VideoTrack>::Create(
42 rtc::Thread::Current(),
43 worker_thread,
44 VideoTrack::Create(
45 receiver_id,
46 VideoTrackSourceProxy::Create(rtc::Thread::Current(),
47 worker_thread,
48 source_),
49 worker_thread))),
50 attachment_id_(GenerateUniqueId()) {
51 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_);
52 SetStreams(streams);
53 source_->SetState(MediaSourceInterface::kLive);
54}
55
56VideoRtpReceiver::~VideoRtpReceiver() {
57 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
58 RTC_DCHECK(stopped_);
59 RTC_DCHECK(!media_channel_);
60}
61
62std::vector<std::string> VideoRtpReceiver::stream_ids() const {
63 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
64 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids(streams_.size());
65 for (size_t i = 0; i < streams_.size(); ++i)
66 stream_ids[i] = streams_[i]->id();
67 return stream_ids;
68}

70rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> VideoRtpReceiver::dtls_transport()
71 const {
72 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
73 return dtls_transport_;

76std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>

78 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);

82RtpParameters VideoRtpReceiver::GetParameters() const {
83 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
84 if (!media_channel_)
85 return RtpParameters();
86 return ssrc_ ? media_channel_->GetRtpReceiveParameters(*ssrc_)
87 : media_channel_->GetDefaultRtpReceiveParameters();
88}

90void VideoRtpReceiver::SetFrameDecryptor(
91 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor) {
92 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
93 frame_decryptor_ = std::move(frame_decryptor);
94 // Special Case: Set the frame decryptor to any value on any existing channel.
95 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_) {
96 media_channel_->SetFrameDecryptor(*ssrc_, frame_decryptor_);
97 }
98}

106void VideoRtpReceiver::SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
107 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
108 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
109 frame_transformer_ = std::move(frame_transformer);
110 if (media_channel_) {
111 media_channel_->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(

116#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
117void VideoRtpReceiver::GenerateKeyFrame()
118{
119 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
120 if (stopped_)
121 return;
122 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
123 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
124 if (media_channel_) {
125 media_channel_->GenerateKeyFrame(ssrc_.value_or(0));
126 }
127 });
128}
129#endif

131void VideoRtpReceiver::Stop() {
132 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
133 // TODO(deadbeef): Need to do more here to fully stop receiving packets.
134
135 if (!stopped_) {
136 source_->SetState(MediaSourceInterface::kEnded);
137 stopped_ = true;
138 }
139
140 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
141 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
142 if (media_channel_) {
143 SetSink(nullptr);
144 SetMediaChannel_w(nullptr);
145 }
146 source_->ClearCallback();
147 });
148}
149
150void VideoRtpReceiver::StopAndEndTrack() {
151 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
152 Stop();
153 track_->internal()->set_ended();
154}
155
156void VideoRtpReceiver::RestartMediaChannel(absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc) {
157 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
158
159 // `stopped_` will be `true` on construction. RestartMediaChannel
160 // can in this case function like "ensure started" and flip `stopped_`
161 // to false.
162
163 // TODO(tommi): Can we restart the media channel without blocking?
164 bool ok = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&, was_stopped =
165 stopped_] {
166 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
167 if (!media_channel_) {
168 // Ignore further negotiations if we've already been stopped and don't
169 // have an associated media channel.
170 RTC_DCHECK(was_stopped);
171 return false; // Can't restart.
172 }
173
174 if (!was_stopped && ssrc_ == ssrc) {
175 // Already running with that ssrc.
176 return true;
177 }
178
179 // Disconnect from the previous ssrc.
180 if (!was_stopped) {
181 SetSink(nullptr);
182 }
183
184 bool encoded_sink_enabled = saved_encoded_sink_enabled_;
185 SetEncodedSinkEnabled(false);
186
187 // Set up the new ssrc.
188 ssrc_ = std::move(ssrc);
189 SetSink(source_->sink());
190 if (encoded_sink_enabled) {
191 SetEncodedSinkEnabled(true);
192 }
193
194 if (frame_transformer_ && media_channel_) {
195 media_channel_->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
196 ssrc_.value_or(0), frame_transformer_);
197 }
198
199 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_) {
200 if (frame_decryptor_) {
201 media_channel_->SetFrameDecryptor(*ssrc_, frame_decryptor_);
202 }
203
204 media_channel_->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(*ssrc_, delay_.GetMs());
205 }
206
207 return true;
208 });
209
210 if (!ok)
211 return;
212
213 stopped_ = false;
214}

217void VideoRtpReceiver::SetSink(rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* sink) {
218 if (ssrc_) {
219 media_channel_->SetSink(*ssrc_, sink);
220 } else {
221 media_channel_->SetDefaultSink(sink);
222 }

225void VideoRtpReceiver::SetupMediaChannel(uint32_t ssrc) {
226 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
227 RestartMediaChannel(ssrc);
228}

230void VideoRtpReceiver::SetupUnsignaledMediaChannel() {
231 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
232 RestartMediaChannel(absl::nullopt);
233}

250
251void VideoRtpReceiver::SetStreams(
252 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>& streams) {
253 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
254 // Remove remote track from any streams that are going away.
255 for (const auto& existing_stream : streams_) {
256 bool removed = true;
257 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
258 if (existing_stream->id() == stream->id()) {
259 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(existing_stream.get(), stream.get());
260 removed = false;
261 break;
262 }
263 }
264 if (removed) {
265 existing_stream->RemoveTrack(track_);
266 }
267 }
268 // Add remote track to any streams that are new.
269 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
270 bool added = true;
271 for (const auto& existing_stream : streams_) {
272 if (stream->id() == existing_stream->id()) {
273 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(stream.get(), existing_stream.get());
274 added = false;
275 break;
276 }
277 }
278 if (added) {
279 stream->AddTrack(track_);
280 }
281 }
282 streams_ = streams;
283}

285void VideoRtpReceiver::SetObserver(RtpReceiverObserverInterface* observer) {
286 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
287 observer_ = observer;
288 // Deliver any notifications the observer may have missed by being set late.
289 if (received_first_packet_ && observer_) {
290 observer_->OnFirstPacketReceived(media_type());
291 }
292}

294void VideoRtpReceiver::SetJitterBufferMinimumDelay(
295 absl::optional<double> delay_seconds) {
296 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
297 delay_.Set(delay_seconds);
298 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_)
299 media_channel_->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(*ssrc_, delay_.GetMs());
300}
301
302void VideoRtpReceiver::SetMediaChannel(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) {
303 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
304 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel == nullptr ||
305 media_channel->media_type() == media_type());
306
307 if (stopped_ && !media_channel)
308 return;
309
310 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
311 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
312 SetMediaChannel_w(media_channel);
313 });
314}
315
316// RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_)
317void VideoRtpReceiver::SetMediaChannel_w(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) {
318 if (media_channel == media_channel_)
319 return;
320
321 bool encoded_sink_enabled = saved_encoded_sink_enabled_;
322 if (encoded_sink_enabled && media_channel_) {
323 // Turn off the old sink, if any.
324 SetEncodedSinkEnabled(false);
325 }
326
327 media_channel_ = static_cast<cricket::VideoMediaChannel*>(media_channel);
328
329 if (media_channel_) {
330 if (saved_generate_keyframe_) {
331 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8694): Stop using 0 to mean unsignalled SSRC
332 media_channel_->GenerateKeyFrame(ssrc_.value_or(0));
333 saved_generate_keyframe_ = false;
334 }
335 if (encoded_sink_enabled) {
336 SetEncodedSinkEnabled(true);
337 }
338 if (frame_transformer_) {
339 media_channel_->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
340 ssrc_.value_or(0), frame_transformer_);
341 }
342 }
343}
344
345void VideoRtpReceiver::NotifyFirstPacketReceived() {
346 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
347 if (observer_) {
348 observer_->OnFirstPacketReceived(media_type());
349 }
350 received_first_packet_ = true;
351}
352
353std::vector<RtpSource> VideoRtpReceiver::GetSources() const {
354 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
355 if (!ssrc_ || !media_channel_)
356 return std::vector<RtpSource>();
357 return media_channel_->GetSources(*ssrc_);
358}
359
360void VideoRtpReceiver::OnGenerateKeyFrame() {
361 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
362 if (!media_channel_) {
363 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
364 << "VideoRtpReceiver::OnGenerateKeyFrame: No video channel exists.";
365 return;
366 }
367 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8694): Stop using 0 to mean unsignalled SSRC
368 media_channel_->GenerateKeyFrame(ssrc_.value_or(0));
369 // We need to remember to request generation of a new key frame if the media
370 // channel changes, because there's no feedback whether the keyframe
371 // generation has completed on the channel.
372 saved_generate_keyframe_ = true;
373}
374
375void VideoRtpReceiver::OnEncodedSinkEnabled(bool enable) {
376 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
377 SetEncodedSinkEnabled(enable);
378 // Always save the latest state of the callback in case the media_channel_
379 // changes.
380 saved_encoded_sink_enabled_ = enable;
381}
382
383// RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_)
384void VideoRtpReceiver::SetEncodedSinkEnabled(bool enable) {
385 if (!media_channel_)
386 return;
387
388 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8694): Stop using 0 to mean unsignalled SSRC
389 const auto ssrc = ssrc_.value_or(0);
390
391 if (enable) {
392 media_channel_->SetRecordableEncodedFrameCallback(
393 ssrc, [source = source_](const RecordableEncodedFrame& frame) {
394 source->BroadcastRecordableEncodedFrame(frame);
395 });
396 } else {
397 media_channel_->ClearRecordableEncodedFrameCallback(ssrc);
398 }
399}
